<i>to the back of his head.</i>

258
00:16:55.180 --> 00:16:57.724
<i>The back of his shirt
was covered in blood.</i>

259
00:16:57.725 --> 00:17:00.728
<i>Nicky was alive
when this jersey was removed.</i>

260
00:17:12.489 --> 00:17:13.781
Holy shit.

261
00:17:13.782 --> 00:17:16.868
This line is bananas.

262
00:17:16.869 --> 00:17:18.911
Morgan. you went
to medical school. right?

263
00:17:18.912 --> 00:17:20.121
Uh. nope. premed.

264
00:17:20.122 --> 00:17:21.205
Great. Want to draw blood.

265
00:17:21.206 --> 00:17:22.248
get that line moving?

266
00:17:22.249 --> 00:17:23.750
Uh. no. thanks.

267
00:17:23.751 --> 00:17:25.668
That wasn't an ask.
that was an order.

268
00:17:25.669 --> 00:17:28.087
but phrased nicely.

269
00:17:28.088 --> 00:17:29.922
Go forth. draw much blood.

270
00:17:29.923 --> 00:17:31.674
<i>Any other time.</i>

271
00:17:31.675 --> 00:17:33.719
<i>that would have been
an exciting endeavor.</i>

272
00:17:34.678 --> 00:17:36.012
Is this records?

273
00:17:36.013 --> 00:17:37.555
Guilty as charged.

274
00:17:37.556 --> 00:17:40.016
I'm looking for a file from '73.

275
00:17:40.017 --> 00:17:42.435
Uh. the Estrada Cartel case.

276
00:17:42.436 --> 00:17:45.064
Started off at vice.
became a homicide.

277
00:17:48.442 --> 00:17:49.942
Camilla Figg.

278
00:17:49.943 --> 00:17:51.277
Guardian of Records
since time immemorial.

279
00:17:51.278 --> 00:17:52.278
And you are?

280
00:17:52.279 --> 00:17:54.238
Detective Maria LaGuerta.

281
00:17:54.239 --> 00:17:57.116
The new girl. We can always use
more estrogen in homicide.

282
00:17:57.117 --> 00:17:59.244
Welcome. Right this way.

283
00:18:02.956 --> 00:18:05.541
Here you go. Everything
you need to know and more.

284
00:18:05.542 --> 00:18:07.376
Real vicious bunch.

285
00:18:07.377 --> 00:18:08.587
Yeah.

286
00:18:12.091 --> 00:18:15.426
Oh. sorry. but do you mind?

287
00:18:15.427 --> 00:18:16.969
Of course.

288
00:18:16.970 --> 00:18:18.610
And don't bother refiling.
I'll handle it.

289
00:18:29.566 --> 00:18:32.820
"One son. Brian Moser.
age seven."

290
00:18:37.324 --> 00:18:38.991
Got what I needed. Thanks.

291
00:18:38.992 --> 00:18:40.953
We aim to please.

292
00:18:46.708 --> 00:18:48.251
All right...

293
00:18:51.839 --> 00:18:54.173
<i>You were right. She came down.</i>

294
00:18:54.174 --> 00:18:55.800
She seem satisfied?

295
00:18:55.801 --> 00:18:58.177
There's no mention of Dexter
in any records.

296
00:18:58.178 --> 00:18:59.846
<i>LaGuerta's off the trail.</i>

297
00:18:59.847 --> 00:19:03.224
Great. Uh. any sign
of what I was looking for?

298
00:19:03.225 --> 00:19:04.225
Brian's youth records
are sealed.

299
00:19:04.226 --> 00:19:05.852
<i>Doubly so</i>

300
00:19:05.853 --> 00:19:07.228
<i>when there's medical records
attached.</i>

301
00:19:07.229 --> 00:19:09.313
- Any forwarding address?
<i>- Nothing.</i>

302
00:19:09.314 --> 00:19:11.065
No arrests.

303
00:19:11.066 --> 00:19:12.608
As far as I can tell.
Brian went to the Tampa facility

304
00:19:12.609 --> 00:19:15.278
<i>shortly after leaving you.</i>

305
00:19:15.279 --> 00:19:18.281
Harry. You all right?

306
00:19:18.282 --> 00:19:20.325
I'm good enough.

307
00:19:38.552 --> 00:19:40.595
The state would prefer

308
00:19:40.596 --> 00:19:42.722
not to separate siblings.

309
00:19:42.723 --> 00:19:45.558
Is there any way you could
foster them as a pair?

310
00:19:45.559 --> 00:19:48.394
Uh. Brian has been
remarkably resilient

311
00:19:48.395 --> 00:19:50.521
considering what
they've been through.

312
00:19:50.522 --> 00:19:52.315
And Dexter.

313
00:19:52.316 --> 00:19:54.901
he hasn't said a word since.

314
00:19:54.902 --> 00:19:56.861
- well...
- How did the boys

315
00:19:56.862 --> 00:19:58.697
come into state custody?

316
00:20:00.699 --> 00:20:03.702
Uh. their mother was. uh...

317
00:20:05.579 --> 00:20:08.164
...part of an undercover
drug case that went south.

318
00:20:09.958 --> 00:20:11.667
She was an informant

319
00:20:11.668 --> 00:20:13.086
and. uh...

320
00:20:14.755 --> 00:20:16.590
...murdered by the cartel.

321
00:20:18.133 --> 00:20:19.425
What about their father?

322
00:20:19.426 --> 00:20:21.093
He's in prison.

323
00:20:21.094 --> 00:20:23.554
Relinquished
all parental rights.

324
00:20:23.555 --> 00:20:25.806
Has zero interest
in being their father.

325
00:20:25.807 --> 00:20:27.266
So. they're on their own?

326
00:20:27.267 --> 00:20:28.435
Yeah.

327
00:20:32.731 --> 00:20:34.607
I need a moment with my husband.

328
00:20:34.608 --> 00:20:37.527
Oh. yeah. Sure.

329
00:20:44.117 --> 00:20:46.161
I just have one question.

330
00:20:47.788 --> 00:20:52.209
Is their mother Laura Moser?

331
00:20:53.669 --> 00:20:55.921
That woman
you had an affair with?

332
00:21:02.135 --> 00:21:03.428
Yes.

333
00:21:16.191 --> 00:21:17.442
Hi.

334
00:21:19.319 --> 00:21:21.446
Do you like firetrucks?

335
00:21:32.541 --> 00:21:34.793
These boys need a mother.

336
00:22:06.867 --> 00:22:08.243
Hello.

337
00:22:10.078 --> 00:22:12.788
Um... Hi. Who are you?

338
00:22:12.789 --> 00:22:14.874
Oh. Sorry.
Yeah. I'm Debra Morgan.

339
00:22:14.875 --> 00:22:16.667
Deb. Harry's daughter.

340
00:22:16.668 --> 00:22:18.836
Maria. I work with your father.

341
00:22:18.837 --> 00:22:20.296
What you working on?

342
00:22:20.297 --> 00:22:22.048
Trying to catch
a possible serial killer.

343
00:22:22.049 --> 00:22:24.383
Like <i>Silence of the Lambs?</i>
Can I see?

344
00:22:24.384 --> 00:22:26.510
I'm sorry. but... no.

345
00:22:26.511 --> 00:22:27.970
Uh. where's your father?

346
00:22:27.971 --> 00:22:29.764
Hey.

347
00:22:29.765 --> 00:22:31.223
You're the other
Morgan kid. right?

348
00:22:31.224 --> 00:22:35.227
Yeah. Deb. You're Tanya?
My brother's boss?

349
00:22:35.228 --> 00:22:37.021
The one and only.

350
00:22:37.022 --> 00:22:40.649
I love the idea of him being
ordered around by a lady boss.

351
00:22:40.650 --> 00:22:42.778
Well. I'm certainly
good at that.

352
00:22:49.117 --> 00:22:50.701
Did you always want to do this?

353
00:22:50.702 --> 00:22:52.745
Good question. No.

354
00:22:52.746 --> 00:22:56.248
When I was your age.
I was all about basketball.

355
00:22:56.249 --> 00:22:58.459
That's kind of tough
when you're fun-sized.

356
00:22:58.460 --> 00:22:59.752
And don't have a dick.

357
00:22:59.753 --> 00:23:01.087
Tell me about it.

358
00:23:01.088 --> 00:23:02.088
Volleyball.

359
00:23:02.089 --> 00:23:03.756
You get it.

360
00:23:03.757 --> 00:23:05.716
Those little moments
where everything works out.

361
00:23:05.717 --> 00:23:08.511
You make a perfect pass
to your forward. They score.

362
00:23:08.512 --> 00:23:09.887
An impossible rebound.

363
00:23:09.888 --> 00:23:11.180
A diving bump
that saves the game.

364
00:23:11.181 --> 00:23:13.557
Fucking-A. Love those times.

365
00:23:13.558 --> 00:23:16.435
Endorphins flood your system.

366
00:23:16.436 --> 00:23:18.270
Singular moments.

367
00:23:18.271 --> 00:23:20.231
It's where happiness happens.

368
00:23:20.232 --> 00:23:22.233
So here.
it's catching criminals.

369
00:23:22.234 --> 00:23:24.568
Solving a mystery that
no one else can figure out?

370
00:23:24.569 --> 00:23:26.071
That's the shit.

371
00:23:27.906 --> 00:23:29.240
You got some blue in your blood?

372
00:23:29.241 --> 00:23:31.075
Considering the family business?

373
00:23:31.076 --> 00:23:33.285
Nah. That's a male Morgan thing.

374
00:23:33.286 --> 00:23:36.122
Hmm. That's too bad.

375
00:23:36.123 --> 00:23:38.708
We could always use
more kickass women around here.

376
00:23:41.086 --> 00:23:42.963
Come back and visit me anytime.

377
00:24:14.327 --> 00:24:15.911
<i>This was not the blood drive</i>

378
00:24:15.912 --> 00:24:17.079
<i>I was hoping for.</i>

379
00:24:17.080 --> 00:24:18.998
<i>Getting Spencer on my table</i>

380
00:24:18.999 --> 00:24:21.000
<i>was going to have to wait.</i>

381
00:24:22.335 --> 00:24:23.502
<i>Or maybe not.</i>

382
00:24:23.503 --> 00:24:24.587
Captain!

383
00:24:24.588 --> 00:24:25.754
I see they've got you doing

384
00:24:25.755 --> 00:24:27.089
everything around here now.

385
00:24:27.090 --> 00:24:29.801
Yeah. Got a spot for you
right here.

386
00:24:38.393 --> 00:24:40.603
Now. you've done this
before. right?

387
00:24:40.604 --> 00:24:42.564
Don't be nervous.

388
00:24:48.403 --> 00:24:50.613
- Steady.
- Mm-hmm.

389
00:24:50.614 --> 00:24:51.781
That's good.

390
00:24:57.370 --> 00:24:59.413
Here. let me move
that up for you.

391
00:24:59.414 --> 00:25:01.208
- Thanks.
- Mm-hmm.

392
00:25:06.296 --> 00:25:07.338
Nice veins.

393
00:25:07.339 --> 00:25:08.632
Hmm.

394
00:25:26.858 --> 00:25:30.069
I can't imagine the pain
you and your wife must be in.

395
00:25:30.070 --> 00:25:31.529
Ex-wife.

396
00:25:31.530 --> 00:25:35.033
Yeah. She's-she's just a wreck.

397
00:25:37.577 --> 00:25:39.078
Did you find anything
at the Tigres house

398
00:25:39.079 --> 00:25:40.788
that could help me find my son?

399
00:25:40.789 --> 00:25:42.581
Want some good news?

400
00:25:42.582 --> 00:25:44.708
- Yeah.
- Blood on Nicky's jersey wasn't

401
00:25:44.709 --> 00:25:46.502
indicative of a fatal wound.

402
00:25:46.503 --> 00:25:48.170
It was only on the front.

403
00:25:48.171 --> 00:25:50.589
And most likely from the...
finger amputation.

404
00:25:50.590 --> 00:25:52.216
Yeah.

405
00:25:52.217 --> 00:25:54.760
<i>He was a better actor
than a cop.</i>

406
00:25:54.761 --> 00:25:56.595
So. he could still be alive?

407
00:25:56.596 --> 00:25:58.806
There's a solid chance he is.

408
00:25:58.807 --> 00:26:01.226
I'll take any hope I can get.

409
00:26:06.314 --> 00:26:08.900
Why do you think the cartel has
targeted children?

410
00:26:11.069 --> 00:26:13.071
They're fucking evil animals.

411
00:26:16.533 --> 00:26:18.492
I couldn't agree more.

412
00:26:18.493 --> 00:26:19.578
Yeah.

413
00:26:20.620 --> 00:26:22.246
People who hurt kids...

414
00:26:22.247 --> 00:26:23.415
Hmm.

415
00:26:25.959 --> 00:26:28.420
<i>Chalked that up to foreplay.</i>

416
00:26:33.091 --> 00:26:34.633
I hope you do a better job

417
00:26:34.634 --> 00:26:36.135
with the cold cases
I assigned you

418
00:26:36.136 --> 00:26:38.262
than you do drawing blood.

419
00:26:38.263 --> 00:26:41.766
Well. actually. hoping to turn
the corner on a big case.

420
00:26:42.726 --> 00:26:45.978
Tonight could even be the night.

421
00:26:45.979 --> 00:26:47.896
Good.

422
00:26:47.897 --> 00:26:50.650
We need some good news
around here.

423
00:26:53.528 --> 00:26:55.113
Oh. Your turn.

424
00:26:56.489 --> 00:26:59.825
Morgan. Consider
your blood drive days over.

425
00:27:02.287 --> 00:27:05.457
<i>Every day we leave
evidence of ourselves behind.</i>

426
00:27:07.375 --> 00:27:08.627
<i>Whether we like it or not.</i>

427
00:27:10.503 --> 00:27:13.213
<i>DNA. hair.</i>

428
00:27:13.214 --> 00:27:14.758
<i>dandruff...</i>

429
00:27:16.176 --> 00:27:17.802
<i>Fingerprints.</i>

430
00:27:20.138 --> 00:27:24.266
<i>Identifiers of who we are.
Where we've been.</i>

431
00:27:24.267 --> 00:27:26.727
Hey. Dex. Can I ask a favor?

432
00:27:26.728 --> 00:27:28.688
What's up?

433
00:27:31.191 --> 00:27:34.693
I... want to donate blood.
For Bobby.

434
00:27:34.694 --> 00:27:36.862
Great.
The line's gone down a lot.

435
00:27:36.863 --> 00:27:39.448
The-the-the thing is...
I-I can't.

436
00:27:39.449 --> 00:27:41.492
I'm sure Bobby'll have
more than enough blood.

437
00:27:41.493 --> 00:27:43.077
That's the problem.

438
00:27:43.078 --> 00:27:45.204
Everyone is doing it.
Hell. even your sister.

439
00:27:45.205 --> 00:27:46.538
People ask questions.

440
00:27:46.539 --> 00:27:47.748
<i>There were some mysteries</i>

441
00:27:47.749 --> 00:27:48.999
<i>even I couldn't fathom.</i>

442
00:27:49.000 --> 00:27:51.627
You know about me. Yeah?

443
00:27:51.628 --> 00:27:53.213
Yeah?

444
00:27:54.214 --> 00:27:57.216
Last month I. uh...

445
00:27:57.217 --> 00:27:59.134
I got a call
from a former partner

446
00:27:59.135 --> 00:28:00.679
who tested positive.

447
00:28:02.430 --> 00:28:03.722
For HIV?

448
00:28:03.723 --> 00:28:04.723
Oh.

449
00:28:04.724 --> 00:28:07.226
Yeah. I-I got tested.

450
00:28:07.227 --> 00:28:09.520
but it-it's still
a few weeks away from results.

451
00:28:09.521 --> 00:28:10.938
<i>This is what happens</i>

452
00:28:10.939 --> 00:28:13.023
<i>to normal people
with big secrets.</i>

453
00:28:13.024 --> 00:28:16.402
<i>It's harder for them
to keep their masks on straight.</i>

454
00:28:16.403 --> 00:28:18.278
I've got you.

455
00:28:31.918 --> 00:28:34.378
<i>It was odd being
the blood giver...</i>

456
00:28:34.379 --> 00:28:36.672
<i>but as a budding master
at keeping secrets.</i>

457
00:28:36.673 --> 00:28:39.551
<i>it felt good to help a novice.</i>

458
00:28:44.723 --> 00:28:46.348
Thanks again.
You're a lifesaver.

459
00:28:46.349 --> 00:28:48.767
<i>I'd never been
called that before.</i>

460
00:28:48.768 --> 00:28:50.145
Have a cookie.

461
00:29:00.947 --> 00:29:02.489
Somebody still hasn't
given blood.

462
00:29:02.490 --> 00:29:04.825
I have an intense fear
of needles.

463
00:29:04.826 --> 00:29:07.119
Specifically when they are
poked into me.

464
00:29:07.120 --> 00:29:08.662
You just haven't been poked
in the right place. my friend.

465
00:29:08.663 --> 00:29:11.373
Yeah.

466
00:29:11.374 --> 00:29:14.585
Thanks anyway.
but I think I have to pass.

467
00:29:14.586 --> 00:29:16.670
I'd hate to faint
in front of the guys.

468
00:29:16.671 --> 00:29:18.172
Listen. intern.
One of our own is in need.

469
00:29:18.173 --> 00:29:19.173
This is what we do.

470
00:29:19.174 --> 00:29:20.550
Which arm?

471
00:29:21.718 --> 00:29:24.053
Left. please.

472
00:29:46.451 --> 00:29:47.951
Can you smile for Mama?

473
00:29:47.952 --> 00:29:49.162
Yes.

474
00:29:50.163 --> 00:29:51.539
What?

475
00:29:53.500 --> 00:29:55.000
Dexie's hungry.

476
00:29:55.001 --> 00:29:56.418
He wants a peanut butter
and jelly sandwich.

477
00:29:56.419 --> 00:29:58.338
Okay.

478
00:30:00.507 --> 00:30:02.841
I'm just gonna put Debbie down.

479
00:30:02.842 --> 00:30:05.637
Okay.

480
00:30:20.026 --> 00:30:21.985
Mommy will be right back.

481
00:30:23.196 --> 00:30:24.863
Shut up.

482
00:30:44.300 --> 00:30:46.803
What are you doing?

483
00:30:52.642 --> 00:30:54.560
Why did you do that?

484
00:30:54.561 --> 00:30:55.854
Too noisy.

485
00:30:56.938 --> 00:30:58.981
Brian. you are in a time-out.

486
00:30:58.982 --> 00:31:01.692
Just stay on the couch
until Harry comes home.

487
00:31:22.714 --> 00:31:26.258
Hey. we got to talk
about what you did to Deb.

488
00:31:26.259 --> 00:31:29.094
That was really dangerous.
and you could've hurt her.

489
00:31:30.471 --> 00:31:32.556
Don't just shrug.

490
00:31:32.557 --> 00:31:34.141
You can't do things like that.

491
00:31:34.142 --> 00:31:36.226
You're not my dad.

492
00:31:36.227 --> 00:31:38.437
Uh. I know.

493
00:31:38.438 --> 00:31:40.272
I'm not.

494
00:31:40.273 --> 00:31:42.107
Doris and I. we're both here

495
00:31:42.108 --> 00:31:44.318
to take care of you
and your brother.

496
00:31:44.319 --> 00:31:47.070
I don't want you to.
I want to go home.

497
00:31:47.071 --> 00:31:48.614
I miss my mom!

498
00:31:48.615 --> 00:31:50.908
Hey. hey.

499
00:31:50.909 --> 00:31:52.189
Look. Hey. Come on.
Take it easy.

500
00:31:53.286 --> 00:31:54.995
I hate this place!

501
00:31:54.996 --> 00:31:57.414
This isn't our home!

502
00:31:57.415 --> 00:31:59.416
I hate you!

503
00:31:59.417 --> 00:32:01.669
I hate all of you!

504
00:32:06.299 --> 00:32:08.259
Leave me alone!

505
00:32:15.266 --> 00:32:16.434
Oh.

506
00:32:18.144 --> 00:32:20.312
I cross-checked
recently released patients

507
00:32:20.313 --> 00:32:22.272
from that Tampa hospital
against our records.

508
00:32:22.273 --> 00:32:23.732
And?

509
00:32:23.733 --> 00:32:25.359
Three have addresses
in Dade County.

510
00:32:25.360 --> 00:32:27.277
two have been arrested.

511
00:32:27.278 --> 00:32:30.155
- I'm gonna give them a visit.
- Hmm. nice work.

512
00:32:30.156 --> 00:32:31.657
Uh. if you don't mind.
I'm gonna go through our files.

513
00:32:31.658 --> 00:32:33.367
see if there's anything
I've missed.

514
00:32:33.368 --> 00:32:34.618
- Do your thing.
- Mm-hmm.

515
00:32:34.619 --> 00:32:36.537
- Keep me posted.
- Will do.

516
00:32:38.831 --> 00:32:40.582
All right.

517
00:32:41.960 --> 00:32:43.835
Raul...

518
00:32:45.546 --> 00:32:47.590
...what did you do to Brian?

519
00:32:56.683 --> 00:32:58.183
All right.

520
00:32:58.184 --> 00:33:00.853
He's an orphan.
Foster care like Brian.

521
00:33:29.090 --> 00:33:31.676
Holy shit.

522
00:33:41.269 --> 00:33:43.062
Fucker is stalking my son.

523
00:33:44.105 --> 00:33:45.982
Oh. my God.

524
